description: Development of the former Power Station for leisure and entertainment purposes to provide: (a) up to 41,805 sq.m. of business floorspace (media offices and post production film studios) (B1); (b) up to two theatres (each 9,290 sq.m.); (c) up to 46,190 sq.m. of product showcase pavilion floorspace; (d) between 500 and 750 flats; (e) two hotels, one for families (up to 32,515 sq.m. and approximately 350 rooms/suites) and one for business (up to 69,675 sq.m. and approximately 700 rooms);  (f) 930 sq.m. of retail floorspace (A1); (g) 3,500 car parking spaces and 80 coach parking spaces;  (h) new vehicular access from Battersea Park Road and additional access points from Kirtling Street and Cringle Street, including widening of sections of Kirtling Street and Battersea Park Road; (i) riverside path and new pier.
site_name: Battersea Power Station and South Lambeth Goods Yard
